          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "EXTB",
                "REC",
                "FPGAM"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " We bombarded targets containing",
                "approximately 10**17 atoms/cm2 of 254Esg with 180 and",
                "22Ne ions at the Lawrence Berkeley Laboratory 88-inch",
                "cyclotron. We counted a single mass-256 fraction for",
                "gamma rays. Reaction products recoiled from the",
                "target and passed through a 50 microg/cm2 aluminum",
                "cover foil and approximately 1 cm of 10 torr helium",
                "cooling gas before they were collected with 3.6",
                "mg/cm2 tantalum or 4.6 mg/cm2 molybdenum foils. The",
                "start of the first data accumulation was 110 min",
                "after the end of the 180 irradiation. The decay of",
                "the sample was followed for 30 h. We observed not",
                "only gamma-ray peaks associated with the decay of",
                "256Esm, but also many gamma rays emitted by the 256Fm",
                "SF fragments. Using known gamma-ray intensities and",
                "decay-curve analysis, we reproduced the mass-yield",
                "curve of the SF decay of 256Fm."
              ]
            }
          ],
